Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 15:57:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: rename 'application logo' to 'application_logo' to fix
 iOS asset loading

The space in the directory name 'application logo' causes iOS to fail
loading these assets when the app is built as an IPA. Renamed the
directory to 'application_logo' and updated all references in:
- pubspec.yaml (asset declarations and flutter_icons config)
- lib/main.dart (splash screen icon)
- lib/screens/widgets/centered_app_bar_title.dart (app bar logo)
- lib/screens/guest/guest_profile_screen.dart (profile logo)
- lib/screens/guest/guest_contacts_screen.dart (contact photos)
- lib/screens/student/student_home_screen.dart (stories logo)

Co-Authored-By: fyob8@sharebot.net <fyob8@sharebot.net>
